<DocsLayout title="ctx_metrics — Session Statistics" description="Real-time token savings with tiktoken-measured counts and file references.">
  <p>
    <code>ctx_metrics</code> displays real-time session statistics including total token savings,
    cache hit rates, and file reference mappings.
  </p>

  <h2>Parameters</h2>
  <p>No parameters. Returns current session statistics.</p>

  <h2>Example Output</h2>
  <pre><code>ctx_metrics

lean-ctx session
files: 12 tracked, 34 reads, 22 hits (65%)
tokens: 28,450 original → 4,120 sent (−24,330 saved, 85%)
refs: F1=auth.ts F2=db.ts F3=routes.ts F4=config.ts</code></pre>

  <h2>Understanding the Output</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>files:</strong> Number of unique files tracked, total reads, and cache hits with hit rate</li>
    <li><strong>tokens:</strong> Original token count (what would have been sent without lean-ctx), actual tokens sent, and the savings in absolute and percentage terms</li>
    <li><strong>refs:</strong> File reference map — shows which <code>F1</code>, <code>F2</code>, etc. labels correspond to which files</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Persistence</h2>
  <p>
    Session data is automatically saved to <code>~/.lean-ctx/stats.json</code> when the MCP server
    exits. Historical data can be viewed in the <a href="/docs/dashboard">Dashboard</a> or via the
    <a href="/docs/cli">CLI</a>.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
